9","score":32}],"links":[{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recF09FMjRr0gzjQk","label":"part of"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recMxoVUt13ExT48g","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recgkzNX07a7kGFYL","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recgkFqZovgbr3pAi","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"reckKYeZ5P0KFuSkB","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recLFwe2uKBqJwmWn","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recjNRR60PAuFtjha","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"rec46MqJI7uxMvviP","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recR67sC02MfTx4al","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recmRfnw4XzPBH9jc","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recAalC2QoLT7cJKN","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recP7b9XZLCwAh5lU","target":"recltAvLmGRfERhYp","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recQjf47gmLhrJeOa","ref":"Acts.26.1","text":"Then Agrippa said unto Paul, Thou art permitted to speak for thyself. Then Paul stretched forth the hand, and answered for himself:","year":62},{"id":"recarlwJgelIMXhmO","ref":"Acts.26.2","text":"I think myself happy, king Agrippa, because I shall answer for myself this day before thee touching all the things whereof I am accused of the Jews:","year":62},{"id":"recvedVn3BrCQgdDk","ref":"Acts.26.3","text":"Especially because I know thee to be expert in all customs and questions which are among the Jews: wherefore I beseech thee to hear me patiently.","year":62},{"id":"recx5WQEWmhkIya7i","ref":"Acts.26.4","text":"My manner of life from my youth, which was at the first among mine own nation at Jerusalem, know all the Jews;","year":62},{"id":"reco6KDVymwjp4jmA","ref":"Acts.26.5","text":"Which knew me from the beginning, if they would testify, that after the most straitest sect of our religion I lived a Pharisee.","year":62},{"id":"recOnBSTbVNM5NCra","ref":"Acts.26.6","text":"And now I stand and am judged for the hope of the promise made of God unto our fathers:","year":62},{"id":"recyuOPftVAnKbKiH","ref":"Acts.26.7","text":"Unto which promise our twelve tribes, instantly serving God day and night, hope to come. For which hope’s sake, king Agrippa, I am accused of the Jews.","year":62},{"id":"rec9FN0bvRxQnDqIx","ref":"Acts.26.8","text":"Why should it be thought a thing incredible with you, that God should raise the dead?","year":62}]}
